spanishExample: Esto solo existe en su mente.
englishTranslation: This only exists in her mind.

spanishExample: Extrañaré el mercado cuando ya no esté abierto.
englishTranslation: I’ll miss the market when it’s not open anymore.

spanishExample: Extrañaba a mi familia.
englishTranslation: I was missing my family.

spanishExample: La extrañas porque eres inteligente.
englishTranslation: You miss her because you’re smart.

spanishExample: No tienes que extrañarnos, estaremos contigo.
englishTranslation: You don’t have to miss us, we’ll be with you.

spanishExample: ¿La extrañaste en el restaurante?
englishTranslation: Did you miss her at the restaurant?

spanishExample: Extraña su gato, por eso soñó con él.
englishTranslation: She misses her cat, that’s why she dreamt about him.

spanishExample: No creo que esa cosa con la que soñé exista.
englishTranslation: I don’t think that thing I dreamt about exists.

spanishExample: Lo extrañamos porque es necesario.
englishTranslation: We miss it because it’s necessary.

spanishExample: Estaba despierto anoche y por eso estoy cansado.
englishTranslation: I was awake last night and that’s why I’m tired.

spanishExample: No puede existir, sería peligroso.
englishTranslation: That can’t exist, it would be dangerous.

spanishExample: Soñaba con cosas falsas.
englishTranslation: I was dreaming about fake things.

spanishExample: Te extrañé en el colegio ayer.
englishTranslation: I missed you at school yesterday.

spanishExample: No sé porque sueño con ella, ya no la extraño.
englishTranslation: I don’t know why I dream about her, I don’t miss her anymore.

spanishExample: Soñaba que era amable conmigo.
englishTranslation: I was dreaming he was kind to me.

spanishExample: No he soñado con el club en meses.
englishTranslation: I haven’t dreamt about the club in months.

spanishExample: No creo que esas estaciones existan más, si existen, deben estar cerradas.
englishTranslation: I don’t think those stations exist anymore; if they exist, they must be closed.

spanishExample: ¿Soñaste con algo dulce?
englishTranslation: Did you dream about something sweet?

spanishExample: Sigue soñando y lo conseguirás.
englishTranslation: Keep dreaming and you’ll get it.

spanishExample: Extrañan a su amigo que está en la cárcel.
englishTranslation: They miss their friend who is in jail.

spanishExample: Te extrañamos en la iglesia la semana pasada.
englishTranslation: We missed you at church last week.

spanishExample: Sueña con algo horrible.
englishTranslation: She dreams about something horrible.

spanishExample: No existía, así que ella no lo extrañaba.
englishTranslation: It didn’t exist, so she didn’t miss it.

spanishExample: Soñar ha existido por mucho tiempo.
englishTranslation: Dreaming has existed for a long time.
